#!/bin/bash
cat << 'EOF'

WeakLink Labs — Available Commands
===================================

Package Management:
  pip install <pkg>            Install a Python package
  pip-audit                    Audit installed packages for vulnerabilities
  pipdeptree                   Show dependency tree
  pip-compile                  Generate lockfile from requirements.in
  npm install <pkg>            Install an npm package
  depcheck                     Check for unused/missing dependencies

Registry Inspection:
  pip index versions <pkg>     Check available versions on configured indexes
  npm view <pkg>               View package metadata from Verdaccio
  npm pack <pkg>               Download and extract a package tarball
  curl http://pypi-private:8080/simple/   Browse private PyPI
  curl http://pypi-public:8080/simple/    Browse public PyPI

Git (Gitea):
  git clone http://gitea:3000/<user>/<repo>.git
  curl http://gitea:3000/api/v1/version   Check Gitea API

Container Registry:
  curl http://registry:5000/v2/_catalog   List images
  curl http://registry:5000/v2/<name>/tags/list   List tags

Configuration:
  cat ~/.config/pip/pip.conf   View pip configuration
  cat ~/.npmrc                 View npm configuration

Tips:
  - Your pip config uses --extra-index-url (vulnerable by design)
  - Fix it by using --index-url with only the private registry
  - Use pip install --no-deps to skip transitive dependencies
  - Use npm --registry=<url> to override the default registry

EOF
